The current test found that if an object configuration in the json column allows null, an exception will occur when querying the column alone. Currently, I can only temporarily solve this problem by manually new()ing all nullable attributes.

```
{"AppName": "优选", "WechatPay": null}
{"AppName": "优选"}
```
In fact, there will be no problem if the null value is not written into the final json during serialization.

```
new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    DefaultIgnoreCondition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull,
}
```
**But there seems to be no place to set this up.**
